{
  "page": "Grotesquerie",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:352px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Yezzan%27s_GrotesquerieJasper_Sandner.png\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/8/82/Yezzan%27s_GrotesquerieJasper_Sandner.png/350px-Yezzan%27s_GrotesquerieJasper_Sandner.png\" width=\"350\" height=\"223\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/8/82/Yezzan%27s_GrotesquerieJasper_Sandner.png/525px-Yezzan%27s_GrotesquerieJasper_Sandner.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/8/82/Yezzan%27s_GrotesquerieJasper_Sandner.png/700px-Yezzan%27s_GrotesquerieJasper_Sandner.png 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Yezzan%27s_GrotesquerieJasper_Sandner.png\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div><a href=\"/index.php/Yezzan_zo_Qaggaz\" title=\"Yezzan zo Qaggaz\">Yezzan's</a> grotequerie includes a <a href=\"/index.php/Two-headed_girl\" title=\"Two-headed girl\">two-headed girl</a>, a <a href=\"/index.php/Goat_boy\" title=\"Goat boy\">goat boy</a>, and a <a href=\"/index.php/Bearded_woman\" title=\"Bearded woman\">bearded woman</a>. Art by Jasper Sandner © FFG</div></div></div>\n<p>A <b>grotesquerie</b> is a collection of \"grotesques\", deformed or freakish people,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd25.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd25.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> and occasional curious specimens.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiaf835_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiaf835-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> Grotesqueries are often owned by <a href=\"/index.php/Slavers\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Slavers\">slavers</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot13.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot13.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Culture\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Culture</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Yezzan.27s_grotequerie\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Yezzan's grotequerie</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Recent_events\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Recent events</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#A_Game_of_Thrones\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Game of Thrones</i></span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#A_Clash_of_Kings\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Clash of Kings</i></span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#A_Dance_with_Dragons\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.3</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Dance with Dragons</i></span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#Quotes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-8\"><a href=\"#See_also\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">See also</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-9\"><a href=\"#Behind_the_scenes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Behind the scenes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-10\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">6</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Culture\">Culture</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Grotesquerie&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Culture\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p><a href=\"/index.php/Smallfolk\" title=\"Smallfolk\">Smallfolk</a> often quietly kill <a href=\"/index.php/Dwarf\" title=\"Dwarf\">dwarf</a> infants, or sell them to a <a href=\"/index.php/Slaver\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Slaver\">slaver</a>'s grotesquerie.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot13.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot13.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Purported \"<a href=\"/index.php/Centaur\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Centaur\">centaur</a> skeletons\" occasionally turn up in grotesqueries.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiaf835_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiaf835-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>One of the <a href=\"/index.php/Triarch_of_Volantis\" title=\"Triarch of Volantis\">triarchs</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/Volantis\" title=\"Volantis\">Volantis</a> has a grotesquerie.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd22.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd22.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span id=\"Yezzan's_grotequerie\"></span><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Yezzan.27s_grotequerie\">Yezzan's grotequerie</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Grotesquerie&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Yezzan&#039;s grotequerie\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p><a href=\"/index.php/Yezzan_zo_Qaggaz\" title=\"Yezzan zo Qaggaz\">Yezzan zo Qaggaz</a>, a <a href=\"/index.php/Wise_Master\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Wise Master\">Wise Master</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/Yunkai\" title=\"Yunkai\">Yunkai</a> and an extremely wealthy slave trader, is obsessed with grotesques. He often purchases <a href=\"/index.php/Slave\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Slave\">slaves</a> with physical deformities to add to his \"collection\". Yezzan's grotequerie includes a <a href=\"/index.php/Goat_boy\" title=\"Goat boy\">boy with hairy, deformed legs resembling a goat's legs</a>, a <a href=\"/index.php/Bearded_woman\" title=\"Bearded woman\">bearded woman</a>, a <a href=\"/index.php/Lackwit\" title=\"Lackwit\">feeble-minded</a> <a href=\"/index.php/Two-headed_girl\" title=\"Two-headed girl\">two-headed girl</a> from <a href=\"/index.php/Mantarys\" title=\"Mantarys\">Mantarys</a>, and a hermaphrodite named <a href=\"/index.php/Sweets\" title=\"Sweets\">Sweets</a>, who also sleeps with him.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd25.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd25.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd47.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd47.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup> Yezzan used to own a <a href=\"/index.php/Giant\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Giant\">giant</a>, who he would make copulate with slave women so he could watch. However, the giant died, and Yezzan would pay much <a href=\"/index.php/Gold\" title=\"Gold\">gold</a> to acquire a new one.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd25.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd25.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> The slaves in Yezzan's collection wear <a href=\"/index.php/Gold\" title=\"Gold\">gilded</a> <a href=\"/index.php/Iron\" title=\"Iron\">iron</a> collars, with his name incised in <a href=\"/index.php/High_Valyrian\" title=\"High Valyrian\">Valyrian glyphs</a>; a pair of tiny bells are affixed below the ears, so the wearer produces a tinkling sound with every step.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd47.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd47.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Recent_events\">Recent events</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Grotesquerie&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Recent events\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Game_of_Thrones\"><i>A Game of Thrones</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Grotesquerie&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Game of Thrones\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>When talking to <a href=\"/index.php/Jon_Snow\" title=\"Jon Snow\">Jon Snow</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Tyrion_Lannister\" title=\"Tyrion Lannister\">Tyrion Lannister</a> reflects on his <a href=\"/index.php/Dwarf\" title=\"Dwarf\">dwarfism</a>, and states that had he been born a <a href=\"/index.php/Peasant\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Peasant\">peasant</a>, he might have been sold to some slaver's grotesquerie.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot13.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot13.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Clash_of_Kings\"><i>A Clash of Kings</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Grotesquerie&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Clash of Kings\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>When meeting Tyrion Lannister during the <a href=\"/index.php/Tourney_on_King_Joffrey%27s_name_day\" title=\"Tourney on King Joffrey&#39;s name day\">tourney</a> on King <a href=\"/index.php/Joffrey_Baratheon\" title=\"Joffrey Baratheon\">Joffrey</a>'s <a href=\"/index.php/Nameday\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Nameday\">nameday</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Sansa_Stark\" title=\"Sansa Stark\">Sansa Stark</a> muses that Tyrion walks like something out of a grotesquerie.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok2.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok2.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>After Queen <a href=\"/index.php/Cersei\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Cersei\">Cersei</a> tells Tyrion she has found his <a href=\"/index.php/Mistress\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Mistress\">mistress</a>, Tyrion tells himself he must be hard and unmoving to pass this test, or else he had better seek out a grotesquerie.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok54.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok54.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Dance_with_Dragons\"><i>A Dance with Dragons</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Grotesquerie&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Dance with Dragons\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:352px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Tyrion_Sweets_and_Penny_by_mylestoyne.png\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/0/04/Tyrion_Sweets_and_Penny_by_mylestoyne.png/350px-Tyrion_Sweets_and_Penny_by_mylestoyne.png\" width=\"350\" height=\"410\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/0/04/Tyrion_Sweets_and_Penny_by_mylestoyne.png/525px-Tyrion_Sweets_and_Penny_by_mylestoyne.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/0/04/Tyrion_Sweets_and_Penny_by_mylestoyne.png/700px-Tyrion_Sweets_and_Penny_by_mylestoyne.png 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Tyrion_Sweets_and_Penny_by_mylestoyne.png\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div><a href=\"/index.php/Tyrion_Lannister\" title=\"Tyrion Lannister\">Tyrion Lannister</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Sweets\" title=\"Sweets\">Sweets</a>, and <a href=\"/index.php/Penny\" title=\"Penny\">Penny</a> in <a href=\"/index.php/Yezzan_zo_Qaggaz\" title=\"Yezzan zo Qaggaz\">Yezzan's</a> grotequerie. Art by mylestoyne ©</div></div></div>\n<p>When <a href=\"/index.php/Haldon\" title=\"Haldon\">Haldon</a> challenges <a href=\"/index.php/Qavo_Nogarys\" title=\"Qavo Nogarys\">Qavo Nogarys</a> to a game of <i><a href=\"/index.php/Cyvasse\" title=\"Cyvasse\">cyvasse</a></i> with Tyrion, Nogarys asks if Tyrion is for sale, as one of the <a href=\"/index.php/Triarch_of_Volantis\" title=\"Triarch of Volantis\">Triarchs</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/Volantis\" title=\"Volantis\">Volantis</a> is seeking to purchase a <i>cyvasse</i>-playing dwarf for his grotesquerie.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd22.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd22.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>During the <a href=\"/index.php/Windblown\" title=\"Windblown\">Windblown</a>'s march to <a href=\"/index.php/Meereen\" title=\"Meereen\">Meereen</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Dick_Straw\" title=\"Dick Straw\">Dick Straw</a> tells <a href=\"/index.php/Quentyn_Martell\" title=\"Quentyn Martell\">Quentyn Martell</a> some of the gossip about <a href=\"/index.php/Yezzan_zo_Qaggaz\" title=\"Yezzan zo Qaggaz\">Yezzan zo Qaggaz</a> and his passion for grotesques.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd25.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd25.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>After Tyrion, <a href=\"/index.php/Penny\" title=\"Penny\">Penny</a>, and <a href=\"/index.php/Jorah_Mormont\" title=\"Jorah Mormont\">Jorah Mormont</a> are captured by slavers, they are bought by Yezzan outside of Meereen. The dwarfs Tyrion and Penny are added to Yezzan's grotesquerie, and are made to perform before his guests.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd47.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd47.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Yezzan becomes deathly ill from the <a href=\"/index.php/Pale_mare\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Pale mare\">pale mare</a> <a href=\"/index.php/Disease\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Disease\">epidemic</a>, and Tyrion, Penny, and Jorah escape to the camp of the <a href=\"/index.php/Second_Sons\" title=\"Second Sons\">Second Sons</a> during the chaos.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd57.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_9-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd57.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup> Afterwards, when Penny listlessly says they were better off with Yezzan, Tyrion lies to her about the rest of Yezzan's \"treasures\", saying that all of them fell victim to the pale mare, though he does not know their actual fate.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd66.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_10-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd66.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes\">Quotes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Grotesquerie&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><b>Jaime:</b> Even if <a href=\"/index.php/Bran_Stark\" title=\"Bran Stark\">the boy</a> does live, he will be a cripple. Worse than a cripple. A grotesque. Give me a good clean death.<br />\n<b>Tyrion:</b> Speaking for the grotesques, I beg to differ. Death is so terribly final, while life is full of possibilities.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot9.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_11-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot9.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-11\">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Jaime_Lannister\" title=\"Jaime Lannister\">Jaime</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Tyrion_Lannister\" title=\"Tyrion Lannister\">Tyrion Lannister</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>Had I been born a <a href=\"/index.php/Smallfolk\" title=\"Smallfolk\">peasant</a>, they might have left me out to die, or sold me to some <a href=\"/index.php/Slaver\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Slaver\">slaver</a>'s grotesquerie. Alas, I was born a <a href=\"/index.php/House_Lannister\" title=\"House Lannister\">Lannister</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/Casterly_Rock\" title=\"Casterly Rock\">Casterly Rock</a>, and the grotesqueries are all the poorer.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot13.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot13.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Tyrion_Lannister\" title=\"Tyrion Lannister\">Tyrion Lannister</a>, to <a href=\"/index.php/Jon_Snow\" title=\"Jon Snow\">Jon Snow</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>Cities were where most <a href=\"/index.php/Dwarf\" title=\"Dwarf\">dwarfs</a> ended up, even those whelped by <a href=\"/index.php/Smallfolk\" title=\"Smallfolk\">Goodwife Bumpkin</a> in the turnip patch. The countryside had no grotesqueries or <a href=\"/index.php/Mummer\" title=\"Mummer\">mummer</a> shows... though it did have wells aplenty, to swallow up unwanted <a href=\"/index.php/Cat\" title=\"Cat\">kittens</a>, three-headed calves, and babes like him.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;thoughts of <a href=\"/index.php/Tyrion_Lannister\" title=\"Tyrion Lannister\">Tyrion Lannister</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><b>Sweets:</b> You are trying to decide if I'm a man or woman. I'm both, and <a href=\"/index.php/Yezzan_zo_Qaggaz\" title=\"Yezzan zo Qaggaz\">master</a> loves me best.<br />\n<b>Tyrion (thinking):</b> A grotesquerie. Somewhere some <a href=\"/index.php/God\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"God\">god</a> is laughing.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd47.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd47.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Sweets\" title=\"Sweets\">Sweets</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Tyrion_Lannister\" title=\"Tyrion Lannister\">Tyrion Lannister</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Grotesquerie&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: See also\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/Menagerie\" title=\"Menagerie\">Menagerie</a>, a collection of animals, often exotic ones.</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Behind_the_scenes\">Behind the scenes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Grotesquerie&amp;action=edit&amp;section=9\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Behind the scenes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>In the real world, since at least the medieval period, deformed people have often been treated as objects of interest and entertainment, and have been collected by royalty or exhibited to crowds.<sup id=\"cite_ref-12\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-12\">&#91;12&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-13\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-13\">&#91;13&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Grotesquerie&amp;action=edit&amp;section=10\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap mw-references-columns\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Radwd25.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd25.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">1.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd25.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\">1.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd25.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\">1.2</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd25.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\">1.3</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons\">A Dance with Dragons</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons-Chapter_25\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons-Chapter 25\">Chapter 25</a>, The Windblown.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtwoiaf835-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiaf835_2-0\">2.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiaf835_2-1\">2.1</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i>, Beyond the Sunset Kingdom&#58; Beyond the Free Cities&#32;(The Grasslands).</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Ragot13.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Ragot13.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\">3.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Ragot13.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-1\">3.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Ragot13.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-2\">3.2</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Ragot13.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-3\">3.3</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Game_of_Thrones\" title=\"A Game of Thrones\">A Game of Thrones</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Game_of_Thrones-Chapter_13\" title=\"A Game of Thrones-Chapter 13\">Chapter 13</a>, Tyrion II.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Radwd14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\">4.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-1\">4.1</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons\">A Dance with Dragons</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons-Chapter_14\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons-Chapter 14\">Chapter 1